e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[An interesting aspect of this report is the sugar cubes. A British
Admiralty Room-40 decipherment of German messages to their agent in Buenos
Aires described a shipment of cultures from Madrid included the information
that the cultures were in "sugar cubes". Now we know why and how. During
WWII the British used the same idea when they prepared a large volume of
dairy cattle nuts into which holes had been drilled and short capillary
tubes filled with anthrax spores inserted. These were to be dropped from
bombers if the need had arisen. Fortunately they were never used. - Mod.MHJ]
